@node IconGad_USAGE "IconGad_plugin: Usage"

    @{b}IconGad plugin@{ub}

    @{b}IconGad plugin@{ub} has these publically accessible methods:

        @{b}PROC init(@{FG shine}iconname@{FG text}) OF icongad_plugin@{ub}

            This is the initailization method.
            You have to call this when you are creating the
            PLUGIN.

            @{FG shine}iconname@{FG text} - The name of the icon
                       (without the ".info" extension)

        @{b}PROC disabled(@{FG shine}value@{FG text}) OF icongad_plugin@{ub}

            Use this method to enable or disable (ghost) the icongad.

            @{FG shine}value@{FG text} - The status of the gadget.
                    TRUE means disabled, while FALSE is enabled.


    See the example source code, @{b}IconGad_demo.e@{ub}, for some actual examples
    of this plugin in use.

@endnode

